Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Credicorp, Ferreyros, Pomalca, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-29T21:04:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/peru-stocks-atacocha-credicorp-ferreyros-pomalca-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rose for a third day, gaining 3.5
percent to 19,636.22. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 3.6
percent to 2,673.19.  Banks and industrial stocks surged after a national poll
showed Congresswoman Keiko Fujimori cut the lead of ex-military
rebel Ollanta Humala before a June 5 presidential runoff, said
Gustavo Urrutia, chief economist at Lima-based brokerage
Inteligo SAB. Humala has pledged to raise mining taxes and
renegotiate free-trade agreements.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of
Grupo Oviedo, jumped 8.9 percent to 49 centimos.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1) 
(FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc.,
climbed 6.8 percent to 3.15 soles.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  ,
Peru’s largest financial services company, rose 6 percent to
$96.64.  Grana y Montero SA (GRAMONC1)  (GRAMONC1 PE), Peru’s largest
construction firm, gained 6 percent to 5.14 soles. Luz del Sur
(LUSURC1 PE), Peru’s largest electricity distributor, rose for a
third day, adding 4.8 percent to 5.66 soles.  Mining stocks gained after metals advanced in New York and
 London .  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, soared 13 percent to 17 cents.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1) 
(MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, rose 6.1
percent to 3.64 soles. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE),
the Lima-based zinc and lead producer, gained 5.8 percent to 91
centimos after first-quarter net income of $9.3 million beat
analysts’ estimates. Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s
largest silver producer, rose 5.1 percent to 3.10 soles.
Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., gained 5.1 percent to
$39.50.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
